00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:31,000
 The porch is always a place for any person regardless of spiritual background.

568
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:34,000
 And yet there are moments in the Bible where really the text is speaking

569
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 very specifically to God's people.

570
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 And this is one of those moments.

571
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 So let me just speak to the Christian.

572
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 I have been a Christian for a very long time.

573
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 When I studied this specific passage years ago,

574
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 what I found was something like a bombshell.

575
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:51,000
 Like it shifted my paradigm completely.

576
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:54,000
 Because what I realized in this moment is Moses is saying,

577
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,000
 "Hey, what is going to distinguish you, set you apart,

578
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:59,000
 is not what you know, it's not what you believe,

579
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 and it's not what you do."

580
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,000
 Well, what is it, Moses?

581
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:07,000
 God's presence distinguishes us from the world.

582
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,000
 That's your second point.

583
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:12,000
 God's presence distinguishes us from the world.

584
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:15,000
 It's not that we're Calvinist or Arminian.

585
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:19,000
 It's not that we believe the sign gifts are present or they're dormant.

586
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 It's not that, well, I'm a part of this denomination

