00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 are none of the ways that Moses is self-identifying here.

592
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,000
 You see, when you study the scriptures,

593
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 all of our heroes of the faith are not known

594
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:46,000
 for the theological tribes that they belonged to.

595
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 What they're known for is that they were with God.

596
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 Like Enoch walked with God. Noah walked with God.

597
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,000
 Abraham was a friend of God.

598
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 Jacob wrestled with God. Moses spoke to God face to face.

599
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 We just read that. Hannah prayed and trusted in God.

600
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 David was a man after God's own heart.

601
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 Elijah met with God. Mary and Martha, they were friends of Jesus.

602
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 And then what you see in the book of Acts is Peter and John,

603
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 they had clearly been with Jesus as attested by the very men

604
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 who put Christ to death.

605
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 In this world, you Christian are not known by your doctrinal distinctive,

606
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 your worship preferences, or what Christian influencer

607
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 you happen to know personally.

608
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:31,000
 What you're meant to be known by is God's presence.

609
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:36,000
 People should look at you and they should say, "You've been with God."

610
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 That should be the reality for you.

611
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 And yet this isn't the case for so many of us.

612
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:46,000
 So many of us, we major in the minors and we minor in the majors.

613
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 What matters most is that we abide in Jesus and we bear the fruit of that abiding.

614
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 That we produce the fruit of the Spirit.

615
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 That we look more like Him.

616
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:58,000
 That we actually exemplify His character to a world that is in desperate need of it.

617
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:03,000
 And what's amazing is that as we do this, what we see is that

618
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 when God's presence becomes the distinguishing force for us personally,

619
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 it becomes the distinguishing force for us communally.

620
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,000
 That's what Paul writes to the Corinthians.

