00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 He says this in 1 Corinthians 3, 16.

622
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 He says, "Do you," and the "you" there is plural.

623
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,000
 It's "y'all."

624
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:26,000
 "Do y'all not know that y'all are God's temple and that God's Spirit dwells in y'all?"

625
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:32,000
 You see, what he's saying is that when you're individually distinguished by God's presence

626
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:35,000
 and we come together, we are communally distinguished by God's presence.

627
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 And that's compelling to the world.

628
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:41,000
 The world looks at it and says, "Man, God must be among you,"

629
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,000
 which is what Paul says later in the book of 1 Corinthians.

