 Psalm 27 says, "You have said, 'Seek my face in my heart.'

729
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:25,000
 The seat of my affections says, 'Your face, Lord, do I seek.'"

730
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 You see, everything we do here is relationally focused

731
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:31,000
 because we're seeking a person when we gather in this room.

732
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 We're meeting with Jesus.

733
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:36,000
 So it shouldn't be the base that stirs our soul.

734
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:41,000
 It should be the words that we sing that stir us instead.

735
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:46,000
 It shouldn't just be some clever story or line I give you that leads to conviction.

736
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:50,000
 It should be a work of the Spirit that produces conviction.

737
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:57,000
 You see, it's not the trappings of ministry that should evoke your feelings.

738
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:03,000
 It's the person of Jesus, the center of Christianity, that should do it instead.

739
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:05,000
 We don't just want to feel something.

740
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:07,000
 In this room, we want to feel someone.

741
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,000
 We want to experience God.

742
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:13,000
 We want to be a people who rightly and really worship God.

743
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:16,000
 Jesus describes it like this in John 4.

744
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:17,000
 He says this to the woman at the well.

745
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:21,000
 He says, "But the hour is coming, and now it's here

746
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:26,000
 when true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit and in truth.

747
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,000
 For the Father is seeking such a people to worship Him."

748
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,000
 Do you catch that?

749
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:33,000
 God is seeking a people that will worship Him in spirit and in truth.

750
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:37,000
 For God is spirit, and those who worship Him must worship Him in spirit and truth.

751
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,000
 So let me ask, which way do you lean?

752
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:41,000
 Do you lean towards truth?

753
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:44,000
 That's good. That's a great thing.

754
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:46,000
 But you should be two at the same time.

755
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,000
 Do you lean towards spirit?

756
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:50,000
 Then you need to add truth to that as well.

757
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:53,000
 God is seeking a people that do both.

758
00:39:53,000 --> 00:40:00,000
 He wants a people that both have a faith of fact and a faith of feeling.

759
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:02,000
 That's what a full-hearted faith looks like.

760
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:05,000
 That leads us to be genuine worshippers.

761
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:07,000
 God is seeking a people like this.

762
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:10,000
 What happens whenever we lean into it and we believe it's true

763
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:14,000
 is we actually start seeking after Him, which is what Moses does next.

764
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:15,000
 This is our final point.

765
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:18,000
 He says in 17 and 18, "And the Lord said to Moses,

766
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:21,000
 'This very thing that you have spoken, I will do,

767
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:24,000
 for you have found favor in my sight, and I know you by name.'"

768
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,000
 God just conceded.

769
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:27,000
 He's like, "Yes, okay. I'll go with you.

770
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,000
 We'll go to the promised land.

771
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,000
 I won't just go with you. I will go with them."

772
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:37,000
 And then Moses says, "Please show me your glory."

773
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:42,000
 I think that this is simultaneously the most confusing yet convicting part

774
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:45,000
 of this story and perhaps one of the most convicting parts

775
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:47,000
 of the entire Bible.

776
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:50,000
 Like Moses just got what he needed.

777
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:53,000
 God just said, "I'll come."

778
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:56,000
 And yet he doesn't stop there.

779
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,000
 Moses goes further.

780
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:05,000
 You see, Moses, he not only needs God in the future,

781
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:07,000
 he wants God in the present.

782
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:11,000
 And the reason for that is because he knows God's presence

783
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:13,000
 is worthy of wanting.

784
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:16,000
 God's presence is worthy of wanting.

785
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:19,000
 Moses makes a major distinction in this moment,

786
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:21,000
 that while God is dependable, he's dependable.

787
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,000
 He can drive out our enemies.

788
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:24,000
 He can bless our people.

789
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,000
 He can distinguish us from the nations.

790
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:30,000
 He's also desirable.

791
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,000
 And here's the thing.

792
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:37,000
 As I say that, I know that some of you are just shaking your head.

793
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,000
 You're like, "Yes, I agree. I know this."

794
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:43,000
 And yet you don't know it as well as you think.

795
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,000
 You see, there's a big difference in saying, "God, I need you,"

796
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:47,000
 and "God, I want you."

797
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:53,000
 Both are good and both are necessary, but both are different.

798
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:57,000
 One is about sustenance and the other is about satisfaction.

799
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:59,000
 So I'll put it to you this way.

800
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:01,000
 Sustenance is about getting what we need.

801
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:04,000
 If you've ever been backpacking, then what you know is

802
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:07,000
 the food you eat on the trail is anything less than a five-course meal.

803
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,000
 Your meals consist of things like mac and dac, you know,

804
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:13,000
 sausage and beans, rice and tuna.

805
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,000
 This is the food you eat. Why?

806
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,000
 Because the goal isn't satisfaction. The goal is sustenance.

807
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,000
 You know what your body needs.

808
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:22,000
 It needs nourishment, and so you're willing to eat

809
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:25,000
 protein and carbs to keep you going down the trail ahead.

810
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:30,000
 And yet, sustenance ends the minute you come off the mountain.

811
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:32,000
 The minute you return to the big city,

812
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:34,000
 your eyes are not looking for that which will nourish my needs.

813
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:38,000
 Instead, you start looking for that which will satisfy my stomach.

814
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:41,000
 You start moving towards that which you want.

815
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,000
 When my friends and I would go backpacking,

816
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:48,000
 we would, in the final few days, dream about what we would eat.

817
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:52,000
 Double cheeseburgers, pizza, meat lovers only,

818
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:55,000
 steak and potatoes, because that's actually the only right answer.

819
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:59,000
 We would start fantasizing about the food we would find,

820
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:02,000
 because long gone were the days of seeking sustenance.

821
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:05,000
 Now was the day of seeking satisfaction.

822
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:10,000
 There's a big difference in pursuing what you need and pursuing what you want.

823
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:14,000
 You see, so many young adults that I visit with,

824
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:17,000
 and I need you to hear me on this,

825
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:20,000
 you have heard repeatedly from this stage and stages like it,

826
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:26,000
 so you know it very well, that Jesus is the source of all satisfaction.

827
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:34,000
 Why then does your relationship only exist around sustenance?

828
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:38,000
 You see, often we come to Jesus on the basis of what we need.

829
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:41,000
 "Jesus, I need your help because I've got this conversation coming up at work,

830
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:44,000
 and my boss is crazy," or "Jesus, I need you to give me some support

831
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,000
 because a conflict with my mom, it never goes well,"

832
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:49,000
 or "Jesus, I need you because my chronic pain, it's crippling."

833
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:53,000
 And listen, Jesus, he delights to be needed.

834
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:55,000
 That is part of the Christian experience.

835
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,000
 Do not be mistaken.

836
00:43:56,000 --> 00:44:00,000
 We need Jesus to save us from our sin, to forgive us of our trespasses,

837
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,000
 to heal us of our hearts, to be the Lord of our life.

838
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:10,000
 We need Jesus, but he is also worthy of wanting.

839
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:16,000
 You see, so very often we need Jesus, but we don't want him.

840
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:19,000
 And the reason for that is because when we're out of options,

841
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,000
 he's always the one we turn to.

842
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:28,000
 But when we have other options, he's seldom, if ever, the one we turn to.

843
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:33,000
 You see, you'll have a free Saturday morning,

844
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:37,000
 and so you'll hit the gym, you'll go to spin, you'll take a brunch,

845
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,000
 you'll do whatever it is that you want,

846
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:41,000
 when in reality, I mean, you actually,

847
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:46,000
 you could take some of that time to read the word.

848
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:50,000
 You'll have some downtime at the office,

849
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:55,000
 and so you'll spend it shopping for a new top for the summer,

850
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:58,000
 for a dress for that wedding, new shoes to add to your collection,

851
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:01,000
 and you'll try to bury it in a million different tabs

852
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:03,000
 so your boss will never know.

853
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:07,000
 And yet, what if you took the time

854
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:11,000
 and you journaled five things you're grateful for to Jesus instead?

855
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:16,000
 You'll have an evening free, for once.

856
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:20,000
 And you could take the evening and you could seek him, pray to him.

857
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,000
 But Love Island just came out two weeks ago,

858
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:25,000
 and I'm already one episode behind.

859
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:28,000
 Listen, we laugh at this stuff, but we do this stuff.

860
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:30,000
 I do this stuff.

861
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:34,000
 We are all a part of this moment together.

862
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:36,000
 Let me be very clear.

863
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:38,000
 Jesus is not trying to guilt trip you.

864
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:41,000
 He's not against your pastimes or your hobbies.

865
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:43,000
 He might be against Love Island,

866
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:48,000
 but what we do know is that Jesus,

867
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:50,000
 he wants to satisfy you,

868
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:54,000
 and yet, if we only ever interact with him out of need,

869
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:57,000
 we should never be expected to be satisfied.

870
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:02,000
 You cannot come to him in moments where you are needing sustenance

871
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:04,000
 and you expect him to give you satisfaction.

872
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:07,000
 You have to come to him when the options are open

873
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:11,000
 and you choose him instead because you want him most.

874
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,000
 A.W. Tozer, one of my favorite quotes says,

875
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:16,000
 "Complacency is a deadly foe of all spiritual growth.

876
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:20,000
 Acute desire, desire, must be present

877
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:23,000
 or there will be no manifestation of Christ to his people.

878
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:26,000
 He waits to be wanted too bad,

879
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,000
 too bad that with many of us,

880
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:32,000
 he waits so long, so very long in vain."

881
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:36,000
 God waits to be wanted, not just needed.

882
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:40,000
 So friends, we shouldn't want for more of God.

883
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:42,000
 Friends, we should want for more of God

884
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:44,000
 and not just need more from God.

885
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,000
 Moses wanted more of God,

886
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:48,000
 and so God gave Moses more of himself.

887
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:49,000
 This is where we'll end.

888
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,000
 In 19 and 20, he said,

889
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,000
 "I will make my goodness pass before you

890
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:54,000
 and will proclaim before you the name of the Lord,

891
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:56,000
 and I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious,

892
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:58,000
 and I'll show mercy on whom I will show mercy,

893
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:01,000
 but," he said, "you can't see my face,

894
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:04,000
 for man shall not see me and live."

895
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:08,000
 Friends, listen, do you want more of God?

896
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,000
 Then you can have him.

897
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,000
 You can have more of God,

898
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:14,000
 and you can have more of God in a way

899
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:17,000
 that Moses himself could not have.

900
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:20,000
 For Moses could not look upon the face of God,

901
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,000
 but we have looked upon the face of God

902
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:25,000
 and that we have seen Jesus Christ himself.

903
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:29,000
 Moses, he knew that he could not see God and live,

904
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:32,000
 and yet those who live have seen God

905
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:36,000
 and that they have seen Jesus himself.

906
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:39,000
 Moses, he asked to see God's glory,

907
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:41,000
 but we have seen God's glory

908
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:44,000
 in that Jesus is the radiance of the glory of God

909
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:48,000
 and the exact imprint of his nature.

910
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:52,000
 You see, we know that.

911
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:57,000
 Jesus always understood God's presence is the point.

912
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:59,000
 God has always longed to be near us,

913
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:01,000
 and in order to make that happen,

914
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:03,000
 Jesus came close to us.

915
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:06,000
 He left heaven, he came to earth,

916
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:08,000
 not just to save someone's general sins,

917
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:10,000
 but to save you from yours.

918
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:13,000
 We know that Jesus understood it's my presence

919
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:14,000
 which will distinguish them,

920
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:17,000
 and so I will live and die and rise

921
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:19,000
 that they might have my presence within them,

922
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,000
 my Holy Spirit that will distinguish them

923
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:23,000
 from the rest of the world.

924
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:26,000
 We can also be convinced that Jesus knew,

925
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:29,000
 man, my presence is worthy of wanting,

926
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:31,000
 but they don't want it.

927
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:35,000
 They don't want it because they do not realize

928
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,000
 that their wanting is warranted,

929
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:39,000
 and so I, I will want them first.

930
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,000
 I will come closest to them,

931
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:44,000
 and by way of me doing so, they will want me,

932
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:47,000
 not just today, not just tomorrow, but forever.

933
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:50,000
 Do you want Jesus here tonight?

934
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:51,000
 We're gonna move into a time

935
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:54,000
 where we're singing in worship

936
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:59,000
 as a declaration of our desire that God, we want you.

937
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:02,000
 If you don't want him, then what you need to know

938
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,000
 is we've got some people down front

939
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:05,000
 that would love to pray with you,

940
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:08,000
 and the walk is awkward, and it's very uncomfortable,

941
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,000
 and yet they would love to process with you

942
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,000
 why you may be lacking in desire,

943
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:14,000
 but we wanna take time over the rest of the evening,

944
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:17,000
 and we just wanna sing, and we wanna respond,

945
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:19,000
 and we wanna rejoice because we believe

946
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:22,000
 not just in head, but in heart

947
00:49:22,000 --> 00:49:23,000
 that he is worthy of wanting,

948
00:49:23,000 --> 00:49:26,000
 and we want to convince him that that's true.

949
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:28,000
 Let me pray that we would.

950
00:49:28,000 --> 00:49:31,000
 Father, we love you.

951
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:32,000
 We said it at the beginning.

952
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:34,000
 We believe that now.

953
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,000
 I'm grateful that your word is so very sufficient,

954
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:40,000
 that Jesus, you have met us in our need,

955
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:46,000
 and now, God, we pray you would cultivate our desire,

956
00:49:46,000 --> 00:49:49,000
 that you would hear from us hearts of worship,

957
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:53,000
 worship of wanting, desire to be near.

958
00:49:53,000 --> 00:49:58,000
 Would the cry of this room be yearning, longing

959
00:49:58,000 --> 00:50:00,000
 to have more of you?

960
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:01,000
 We sing to you now.

961
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:04,000
 It's in Jesus' name, amen.

962
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:06,000
 You can stand where you are,

963
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:09,000
 and you can respond as you feel led.

